alist and associate fellow of [[Chatham House]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chathamhouse.org/about-us/directory/70632#|title=Nicholas Shaxson|work=Chatham House|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Ben Anderson (journalist)|Ben Anderson]] (born 1975), television reporter and writer (''[[Holidays in the Axis of Evil]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n\n==Law==\n[[File:William Robert Bousfield.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[William Robert Bousfield|W. R. Bousfield]]]]\n* [[William Robert Bousfield]] [[Queen's Counsel|KC]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (1854\u20131943)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Sir William Tudball]] (1866\u20131943). [[Puisne judge]] of the High Court of [[Allahabad]] (1909\u20131922)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Sir William Tudball'', 24 April 1939, p.14</ref>\n* [[Sidney Abrahams|Sir Sidney Abrahams]] [[Queen's Counsel|KC]] (1885\u20131957), Chief Justice of [[Tanganyika]] and [[Sri Lanka|Ceylon]]; Privy Councillor<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Sir Clement Thornton Hallam]] (1891\u20131965), Solicitor to the [[General Post Office]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[James Mould (lawyer)|Dr James Mould QC]] (1893\u20131958), [[Queen's Counsel]], Bencher of Gray's Inn and a Fellow of [[University College London]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. James Mould'', 7 April 1958, p.9</ref>\n* [[Stephen John Wooler]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (born 1948), HM Chief Inspector to the [[Crown Prosecution Service]] (1999\u20132010)<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Nicholas Stewart (lawyer)|Nicholas Stewart]] [[Queen's Counsel|QC]] (born 1947), [[Queen's Counsel]], [[Bencher]] of the [[Inner Temple]], Deputy [[High Court judge (England and Wales)|High Court Judge]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Tim Lord|Hon. Tim Lord]] [[Queen's Counsel|QC]] (born 1966), [[Barrister]], [[Queen's Counsel]] and [[Bencher]] of the [[Inner Temple]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\n==Literature==\n[[File:William Hale White00.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Hale White|William Hale White]]]]\n* [[Hale White|William Hale White]] (1831\u20131913), author known by his pseudonym Mark Rutherford<ref>{{cite web|url=http://virtual-library.culturalservices.net/webingres/bedfordshire/vlib/0.digitised_resources/bedford_digitisation_people_rutherford_about.htm|title=Mark Rutherford (William Hale White) \u2013 Digitised Resources \u2013 The Virtual Library|author=Bedford Borough Council and Central Bedfordshire Council|work=culturalservices.net|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Neil Wynn Williams]] (1864\u20131940), novelist, writer and contributor of short stories and articles to periodicals and journals<ref>School of the Black and Red, A History of Bedford Modern School, by Andrew Underwood, 1981.  Updated by Peter Boon, 2010. Paperback, P.294</ref>\n* [[George Moreby Acklom]] (1870\u20131959), writer, literary editor of [[E.P. Dutton]], father of the Hollywood actor [[David Manners]]<ref>School of the Black & Red, A.G. Underwood (updated 2010), p.104</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.davidmanners.com/biography.html|title=David Manners Biography|work=davidmanners.com|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Henry Howarth Bashford|Sir Henry Howarth Bashford]] (1880\u20131961), author of ''[[Augustus Carp, Esq.]]'' and several other satirical novels<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Eric Temple Bell]], (1883\u20131960), science fiction author (as John Taine)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www-history.mcs.st-and.ac.uk/Biographies/Bell.html|title=Bell biography|work=st-and.ac.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[David Scott Daniell]] (1906\u20131965), author, playwright and regimental historian<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bearalley.blogspot.com/2006/10/richard-bowood-albert-scott-daniell.html|title=Bear Alley: Richard Bowood (Albert Scott Daniell)|author=Steve|work=bearalley.blogspot.com|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=2006-10-14}}</ref>\n* [[Christopher Fry]] (1907\u20132005), poet and playwright. Awarded the [[Queen's Gold Medal for Poetry]] in 1962<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095837104|title=Christopher Fry|work=oxfordreference.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Gordon Thomas (author)|Gordon Thomas]] (1933\u20132017), investigative journalist and author (''[[Gideon's Spies]]'', ''[[The Pope's Jews]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/author/show/48435.Gordon_Thomas|title=Gordon Thomas|author=Gordon Thomas|work=Goodreads|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[John Andrews (writer)|John Andrews]] (born 1936), author and antiques writer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecra.co.uk/find-an-author/john-malcolm/|title=John Malcolm|work=The Crime Readers' Association|accessdate=30 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150622203937/http://www.thecra.co.uk/find-an-author/john-malcolm/|archive-date=22 June 2015|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[David Morse (writer)|David Morse]] (born 1938), author on [[Motown]], [[Romanticism]] and the [[Victorian era]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Russell Ash]] (1946\u20132010), author (''[[The Top 10 of Everything]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scotsman.com/news/obituaries/obituary-russell-ash-1-816754|title=Obituary: Russell Ash|work=scotsman.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[S.I. Martin]] (born 1961), author, historian and journalist specialising in [[Black British]] history and literature<ref>{{cite web|url=http://literature.britishcouncil.org/s-i-martin|title=S. I. Martin \u2013 British Council Literature|author=British Council|work=britishcouncil.org|accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.academia.edu/7333251|title=S.I. Martin, April 24, 1961\u2013 |author=Leila Kamali|journal=Academia.edu|accessdate=28 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Stephen May (novelist)|Stephen May]] (born 1964), novelist, playwright and TV writer<ref>Eagle News, Vol 5 No 4 (Issue 105) May 2012, p.115</ref>\n* [[Toby Litt]] (born 1968), author (''[[Beatniks (novel)|Beatniks]]'', ''[[Corpsing (novel)|Corpsing]]'', ''[[Finding Myself]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n\n==Medicine==\n[[File:George Cleghorn (1850-1902).JPG|thumb|115px|right|[[George Cleghorn]]]]\n[[File:Walter Jessop.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Walter Jessop (surgeon)|Walter Jessop FRCS]]]]\n* [[George Cleghorn]] (1850\u20131902), President of the [[New Zealand Medical Association]]<ref>Obituary notice: George Cleghorn M.D. ''The Eagle'', vol. viii, no. 8, July 1903, pp. 338\u201339</ref>\n* [[Walter Jessop (surgeon)|Walter Jessop]] [[Royal College of Surgeons|FRCS]] (1853\u20131917), [[Ophthalmology|Ophthalmic Surgeon]] at [[St Bartholomew's Hospital|St Bartholomew's]], President of the UK Ophthalmological Society<ref>{{cite web|url=http://livesonline.rcseng.ac.uk/biogs/E002362b.htm|title=Jessop, Walter Hamilton Hylton \u2013 Biographical entry \u2013 Plarr's Lives of the Fellows Online|work=rcseng.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Major-General Harold Percy Waller Barrow]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1856\u20131957), Honorary Surgeon to King [[George V]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ramc-ww1.com/profile.php?cPath=211_655&profile_id=9982&osCsid=29|title=RAMC: Royal Army Medical Corps WW1|work=ramc-ww1.com|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[George Harris (physician)|Major-General George Francis Angelo Harris]] [[Order of the Star of India|CSI]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] (1856\u20131931), Professor at the Calcutta Medical School<ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/2048|title=Munks Roll Details for George Francis Angelo Harris|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary, ''Major-General Harris'', ''[[The Times]]'', 18 April 1931, p.12</ref>\n* [[Rickard William Lloyd]] [[Membership of the Royal College of Surgeons|MRCS]] LRCPEd (1859\u20131933), Consulting [[Anesthesiologist|An