330)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''The Times'', ''Mr Frederick Williamson'', 19 November 1935, p.19</ref>\n* [[Reginald Philip Abigail]] (1892\u20131969), [[District Commissioner (British Colonial)|District Commissioner]] of [[Rakhine State|Arakan]] during the [[Japanese conquest of Burma|fall of Burma]] in 1942<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=PKIWAQAAIAAJ&dq=reginald+abigail+burma+kellys&q=abigail+bedford+modern|title=Kelly's Handbook to the Titled, Landed and Official Classes|accessdate=14 June 2015|year=1969|last1=Kelly's}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=oCUbAQAAIAAJ&dq=punjab+bedford+modern&q=abigail+bedford+modern|title=The India Office and Burma Office List|accessdate=14 June 2015|year=1947}}</ref>\n* [[Bertram St. Leger Ten Broeke]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1895\u20131962), Deputy Inspector-General of the Indian Police in [[Bihar]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/story/84029|title=Story: Bedford Modern School Eagle Magazine Obituary for B St L Ten-Broeke, CIE, MC died November 1962 &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[W. D. Harverson]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Royal School of Mines|ARSM]] [[Institute of Materials, Minerals and Mining|MIMM]] (1903\u201392), Commissioner of Mines in [[Kenya]] (1949\u201358) and [[Tanganyika]] (1958\u201362)<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=W11zAAAAMAAJ&dq=author+educated+bedford+modern&q=bedford+modern|title=An encyclopaedia of New Zealand|accessdate=6 June 2015|year=1966|last1=McLintock|first1=Alexander H.}}</ref>\n* [[Walter Ian James Wallace]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1905\u20131993), Assistant Undersecretary of State at the [[Colonial Office]] (1962\u201366)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Arthur Mooring|Sir Arthur Mooring]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|KCMG]] (