Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Herbert Cecil Potter|Brigadier-General Herbert Cecil Potter]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1875\u20131964)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Charles Temple Morris|Colonel Charles Temple Morris]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1876\u20131956), Commander of the 5th Battalion of the [[1st Punjab Regiment]] between 1921 and 1926<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mocavo.com/Whos-Who-Men-and-Women-of-the-Time-1935/107381/2979#2436|title=Whos Who, Men and Women of the Time, 1935|work=Mocavo|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[James Meldrum Knox|Lieutenant-Colonel James Knox]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] (1878\u20131918), Battalion Commander, [[Royal Warwickshire Regiment]], 1915\u201318<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School''(Bedford, no date), p. 72</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Lieutenant-Colonel J.M. Knox D.S.O., Royal Warwick Regiment'', 3 October 1918, p.3</ref>\n* [[Herbert Thomas Dobbin|Brigadier-General Herbert Dobbin]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131946), [[Colonel-Commandant]], [[Iraq Levies]], the [[Duke of Cornwall's Light Infantry]]<ref>''Who was Who Vol. IV, 1941\u201350'' (London, 1980), p. 319.</ref>\n* [[Arthur Turner (British Army officer)|Brigadier-General Arthur Turner]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131952), [[Cricket]]er, [[rugby union]] player and soldier<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/player/21615.html|title=Arthur Turner|work=Cricinfo|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Wilfrid Stanley Richmond|Colonel Wilfrid Stanley Richmond]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|MICE]] (1881\u20131962), Deputy Director of Roads in the [[British Expeditionary Force (World War I)|BEF]] during [[World Wa