'''3\u20131'''\n|-\n| [[2008\u201309 UEFA Champions League#Second qualifying round|2QR]]\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[FC Dynamo Kyiv|Dynamo Kyiv]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\u20132\n| bgcolor=\"#ffffdd\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\u20132\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''3\u20134'''\n|-\n| [[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League|2013\u201314]]\n| [[UEFA Europa League]] \n| [[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|1QR]]\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Sweden}} [[Malm\u00f6 FF|Malm\u00f6]]\n| bgcolor=\"#ffffdd\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\u20130\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\u20132\n| bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''0\u20132'''\n|}\n\n===Statistics===\n[[Graham Gartland]] has the most appearances for the club in European competitions having appeared a record 12 (twelve) times in Drogheda's colours in [[UEFA]] competitions. He also is tied with [[Eamon Zayed]], on 3 (three) goals, as Drogheda United's leading goalscorer(s) in [[UEFA]] competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/teamsandplayers/teams/club=52378/profile/index.html|title=Drogheda \u2013 UEFA.com|first=|last=uefa.com|date=|website=Uefa.com}}</ref>\n\nFinnish international [[Markus Halsti]] has played against Drogheda in four matches, lining out with both HJK and Malm\u00f6.\n\nAlso worth noting is that another former Drogheda player [[Ollie Cahill]] holds the joint record with [[Owen Heary]] for the most appearances in European competition for an Irish domestic player (41). He scored against [[NK Olimpija Ljubljana (1911)|Olimpija Ljubljana]] in August 2003<ref>[http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/archive/2003/0829/Pg021.html#Ar02101:0905640EE5890895990B15A70CD6220FA6370F96221096370E07B111C7C70906720D2688]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121017063601/http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/archive/2003/0829/Pg021.html |date=17 October 2012 }}</ref> and again for Drogheda against [[FC Levadia Tallinn|Levadia Tallinn]] on 16 July 2008 in a [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] qualifier.<ref>[http://www.eircomloi.ie/news-centre/news-1/july-2008/news-40/index.xml] {{Dead link|date=May 2017|}}</ref>\n\n== Records ==\n\n===Most League goals===\n\n(Players in bold still playing for Drogheda)\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!#\n!Name\n!Career\n!Goals\n|-\n|1\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Declan O'Brien (footballer)|Declan O'Brien]]\n|2002\u201308, 2012\u201314 \n|108\n|-\n|2\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} Gel Martin\n|1972\u201386, 1987\u201389\n|52\n|-\n|3\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Damien Byrne]]\n|1974\u201383\n|47\n|-\n|4\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Jerome Clarke]]\n|1968\u201380\n|45\n|-\n|5\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Cathal Muckian]]\n|1972\u201378\n|40\n|-\n|6\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Andrew Myler|Andy Myler]]\n|2002\u201304\n|33\n|-\n|7\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} Paddy Dillon\n|198?\u201386\n|30\n|-\n|8\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} Barry O'Connor\n|1992\u201396\n|29\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|9\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} Denis Stephens\n|1973\u201377\n|27\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} Gerry Brammeld\n|1973\u201379 (or 1980)\n|27\n|-\n|11\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} Martin Murray\n|1982\u201386\n|25\n|-\n|12\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Ireland}} [[Gavin Brennan]]\n|2010\u20132014\n|20\n|-\n|}\n\n===Other records===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | Most points in a season\n| 68: 2007\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | Largest league win\n| 8-1: vs [[Wexford F.C.]], 16 March 2018\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | Heaviest league defeat\n| 1\u20138: vs [[Cork Hibernians F.C.|Cork Hibernians]], 30 January 1972\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | Highest Goalscorer\n| [[Declan O'Brien (footballer)|Declan O'Brien]]: 108, 2002\u201308, 2012