h]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1919]]\n[[Category:Former League of Ireland Premier Division clubs]]\n[[Category:Sport in Drogheda]]\n[[Category:1919 establishments in Ireland]]\n[[Category:League of Ireland First Division clubs]]\n", "name_user": "ChrisTheDude", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e1919\u20131975: Early Years:caps", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drogheda_United_F.C."}
{"title_page": "The Emily Dickinson Journal", "text_new": "{{Infobox Journal\n| cover = [[File:Emily dickinson journal.gif|Image: Emily dickinson journal.gif]]\n| discipline = [[Literature]]\n| abbreviation = Emily Dickinson J.\n| editor = James Guthrie\n| website = http://www.press.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/\n| publisher = [[Johns Hopkins University Press]]\n| frequency = Biannually\n| country = United States\n| link1 = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/\n| link1-name = Online access\n| history = 1991\u2013present\n| ISSN = 1059-6879\n| eISSN = 1096-858X\n| OCLC = 37937179\n| RSS = http://feeds.muse.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/latest_issues.xml\n}}\n'''''The Emily Dickinson Journal''''' ('''''EDJ''''') is a biannual [[academic journal]] founded in 1991 and is the official publication of the [[Emily Dickinson International Society]]. The journal provides an ongoing examination of [[Emily Dickinson]], one of the most influential [[American poetry|American poets]], and her place in literature. The current [[Editor-in-chief|editor]] is [[Cristanne Miller]] ([[University at Buffalo, The State University of New York]]). She is interested in expanding the Journal to encompass Dickinson's relations to 19th-century American studies as well as Dickinson's impact on 20th-century poets. The journal is published by the [[Johns Hopkins University Press]] receives submissions internationally. \n<ref>http://www.pomona.edu/news/2005/11/01-understanding-emily.aspx</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.press.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060709134334/http://www.cwru.edu/affil/edis/edisindex.html Emily Dickinson International Society]\n* [http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/ ''The Emily Dickinson Journal''] at [[Project MUSE]]\n\n{{Emily Dickinson}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Emily Dickinson Journal, The}}\n[[Category:American literary magazines]]\n[[Category:Periodicals about writers|Dickinson, Emily]]\n[[Category:Emily Dickinson]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 1991]]\n[[Category:Johns Hopkins University Press academic journals]]\n[[Category:English-language journals]]\n[[Category:Biannual journals]]\n\n\n{{lit-journal-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Journal\n| cover = [[File:Emily dickinson journal.gif|Image: Emily dickinson journal.gif]]\n| discipline = [[Literature]]\n| abbreviation = Emily Dickinson J.\n| editor = [[Cristanne Miller]]\n| website = http://www.press.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/\n| publisher = [[Johns Hopkins University Press]]\n| frequency = Biannually\n| country = United States\n| link1 = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/\n| link1-name = Online access\n| history = 1991\u2013present\n| ISSN = 1059-6879\n| eISSN = 1096-858X\n| OCLC = 37937179\n| RSS = http://feeds.muse.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/latest_issues.xml\n}}\n'''''The Emily Dickinson Journal''''' ('''''EDJ''''') is a biannual [[academic journal]] founded in 1991 and is the official publication of the [[Emily Dickinson International Society]]. The journal provides an ongoing examination of [[Emily Dickinson]], one of the most influential [[American poetry|American poets]], and her place in literature. The current [[Editor-in-chief|editor]] is [[Cristanne Miller]] ([[University at Buffalo, The State University of New York]]). She is interested in expanding the Journal to encompass Dickinson's relations to 19th-century American studies as well as Dickinson's impact on 20th-century poets. The journal is published by the [[Johns Hopkins University Press]] receives submissions internationally. \n<ref>http://www.pomona.edu/news/2005/11/01-understanding-emily.aspx</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.press.jhu.edu/journals/emily_dickinson_journal/}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060709134334/http://www.