9: Relentless]]\n|{{dts|2010|Feb|6}}\n|[[Mandalay Bay Events Center]]\n|[[Las Vegas]], U.S.\n|{{nts|10753}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/news/17963/ufc-109-relentless-draws-offical-attendance-of-10753-for-2-27-million-gate.mma |title=\"UFC 109: Relentless\" draws official attendance of 10,753 for $2.27 million gate |publisher=mmajunkie.com |date=Feb 16, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120630015354/http://mmajunkie.com/news/17963/ufc-109-relentless-draws-offical-attendance-of-10753-for-2-27-million-gate.mma |archivedate=2012-06-30 }}</ref>\n|-\n|144\n|{{sort|UFC Fight Night 20|[[UFC Fight Night: Maynard vs. Diaz]]}}\n|{{dts|2010|Jan|11}}\n|[[Patriot Center]]\n|[[Fairfax, Virginia]], U.S.\n|{{nts|8078}}<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://mmajunkie.com/news/17524/ufc-fight-night-20-a-sellout-with-near-record-730000-live-gate.mma \n |title=UFC Fight Night 20 a sellout with near-record $730,000 live gate \n |publisher=mmajunkie.com \n |date=Jan 12, 2010 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014024247/http://mmajunkie.com/news/17524/ufc-fight-night-20-a-sellout-with-near-record-730000-live-gate.mma \n |archivedate=2012-10-14 \n}}</ref>\n|-\n|143\n|[[UFC 108|UFC 108: Evans vs. Silva]]\n|{{dts|2010|Jan|2}}\n|[[MGM Grand Garden Arena]]\n|[[Las Vegas]], U.S.\n|{{nts|13529}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/news/17638/ufc-108-scores-offical-attendance-of-13529-for-1-97-million-gate.mma |title=UFC 108 draws official attendance of 13,529 for $1.97 million gate |publisher=mmajunkie.com |date=Jan 21, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120630015433/http://mmajunkie.com/news/17638/ufc-108-scores-offical-attendance-of-13529-for-1-97-million-gate.mma |archivedate=2012-06-30 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Ultimate Fighting Championship|UFC]]\n* [[List of UFC champions]]\n* [[List of UFC events]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Ultimate Fighting Championship}}\n{{UFC Events}}\n\n[[Category:Years in Ultimate Fighting Championship]]\n[[Category:2010 in mixed martial arts]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|UFC MMA events in 2010}}\n{{Year in UFC\n|name = 2010 in UFC\n|image = Logo of the Ultimate Fighting Championship.svg\n|image_size = 176px\n|first_date = January 2, 2010\n|last_date = December 11, 2010\n|total_events = 24\n|numbered_events = 17\n|versus_events = 2\n|fight_night_events = 3\n|tuf_finale_events = 2\n|total_fights = 255\n|title_fights = 10\n|preceded_by = [[2009 in UFC]]\n|followed_by = [[2011 in UFC]]\n}}\n\nThe year '''2010''' is the 18th year in the history of the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC), a [[mixed martial arts]] promotion based in the United States. In 2010 the UFC held 24 events beginning with, ''UFC 108: Evans vs. Silva''.\n\n{{TOClimit|2}}\n\n==Title fights==\n{{MMAtitle}}\n{{MMAtitle card|[[List of UFC champions|Title fights in 2010]]}}\n{{MMAtitle bout\n| Heavyweight\n| [[Shane Carwin]]\n| def.\n| [[Frank Mir]]\n| KO (punches)\n| 1\n| 3:48\n| [[UFC 111]]\n|\n}}\n{{MMAtitle bout\n| Welterweight\n| [[Georges St-Pierre]] (c)\n| def.\n| [[Dan Hardy]]\n| Decision (unanimous) (50\u201343, 50\u201344, 50\u201345)\n| 5\n| 5:00\n| [[UFC 111]]\n| \n}}\n{{MMAtitle bout\n| Lightweight\n| [[Frankie Edgar]]\n| def.\n| [[B.J. Penn]] (c)\n| Decision (unanimous) (50\u201345, 48\u201347, 49\u201346)\n| 5\n| 5:00\n| [[UFC 112]]\n| \n}}\n{{MMAtitle bout\n| Middleweight\n| [[Anderson Silva]] (c)\n| def.\n| [[Demian Maia]]\n| Decision (unanimous) (49\u201347, 48\u201347, 49\u201346)\n| 5\n| 5:00\n| [[UFC 112]]\n| \n}}\n{{MMAtitle bout\n| Light Heavyweight\n| [[Maur\u00edcio Rua]]\n| def.\n| [[Lyoto Machida]] (c)\n| KO (punches)\n| 1\n| 3:35\n| [[UFC 113]]\n| \n}}\n{{MMAtitle bout\n| Heavyweight\n| [[Brock Lesnar]] (c)\n| def.\n| [[Shane Carwin]] (ic)\n| Submission (arm-triangle choke)\n| 2\n| 2:19\n| [[UFC 116]]\n| \n}}\n{{MMAtitle bout\n| Middleweight\n| [[Anderson Silva]] (c)\n| def\n| [[Chael Sonnen]]\n| Submission (triangle armbar)\n